      "content": "The idea that higher wages lead to increased consumer spending is a myth perpetuated by liberal economists. The reality is that a significant portion of the increased wages goes towards debt repayment, savings, and other non-consumer expenses, leaving little to no additional disposable income for local businesses. In fact, studies have shown that higher minimum wages often lead to reduced employment, particularly among low-skilled workers, as businesses are forced to cut back on labor costs or pass the increased expenses on to consumers.",
